data.description: Fantastic opportunity in Baltimore’s Historic Pigtown. An eclectic mix of shops, parks, restaurants and just minutes from Carroll Park this is one Baltimore’s most eclectic and charming neighborhoods. 1260 James St. welcomes you home with a warm and inviting great room. Black wrought iron railings combine with modern grays and white molding throughout to create a uniquely contemporary feel. A partially exposed brick wall and tray ceiling add to the charm. Your gourmet kitchen features beautiful granite countertops, spacious cabinetry, separate island and just installed new gas range and refrigerator. A half bath and washer/dryer complete the first level. The lower level is made up of a full, huge finished basement with a separate utility room that could also accommodate a home office, or craft/work room. Ascending the stairs to the sleeping quarters you will love the skylight that fills the space with natural light even on a cloudy day. The two bedrooms both feature en suite bathrooms and large closets. Off the back bedroom is a quiet deck leading to the stairs to your rooftop deck complete with stunning views of the City and stadiums.  Located minutes from I-95 and 295, and nestled between M&T Bank Stadium, Oriole Park at Camden Yards, and the University of Maryland - Baltimore.
